[{"sha":"6394d3c186602777f7a1ee942316afa2918a3362","author":{"name":"A. Unique TensorFlower","email":"746aced590a184ef4169166e753f7c211e32e5fc@tensorflow.org"},"message":"Workaround MSVC2015 internal compiler errors when building Eigen.

Eigen/src/Core/ArithmeticSequence.h causes an internal compiler
error when building with MSVC2015 with the default built
configuration. This is caused by MSVC2015's partial support for
C++14 which is required by dependencies of TF Lite. To workaround
this issue, limit Eigen to C++11 by defining EIGEN_MAX_CPP_VER=11
when building TF Lite.

Change-Id: I62591057120084a4b4617cb93e84d16ccc520c50","distinct":true,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Mu-L/tensorflow/commits/6394d3c186602777f7a1ee942316afa2918a3362"},{"sha":"d24f1369180d52d0ad79db5fd4df369776c2dc14","author":{"name":"A. Unique TensorFlower","email":"746aced590a184ef4169166e753f7c211e32e5fc@tensorflow.org"},"message":"Workaround MSVC2015 function template expansion in elementwise.

Given a function...
template<int T>
int Foo(int b)

And...
typedef int(*Bar)(int);

MSVC2015 will not see Foo<10> as the same type as Bar.

This works around the issue by instantiating wrapper methods around
elementwise::GenericPrepare() rather than using a templated
elementwise::GenericPrepare method.

Change-Id: I5378de791111b5c75592eacd0b832589252350cf","distinct":true,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Mu-L/tensorflow/commits/e83a3dbda8286609ffb8ce793fcc65dbc35c3387"},{"sha":"839928c4fcaca95eb540101f5f93a060e0995996","author":{"name":"Scott Zhu","email":"65d81eb4203ec9a5a8b298abc5184127125bc9fe@google.com"},"message":"Update keras metrics to use memory efficient alternative when collect values for evenly distributed thresholds.

This implementation is based on the example in tf.slim. It exhibits a run time and space complexity of O(T + N), where T is the number of thresholds and N is the size of predictions. Metrics that rely on standard implementation instead exhibit a complexity of O(T * N). It could save a lot of memory when N is large.

Added a unit test to verify the memory consumption. Under eager context, the ratio of memory between old and new approach is between 80 and 500. Set the limit to 50 to avoid the flakiness.

Unique TensorFlower","email":"746aced590a184ef4169166e753f7c211e32e5fc@tensorflow.org"},"message":"Workaround MSVC2015 internal compiler errors when building Eigen.

Eigen/src/Core/ArithmeticSequence.h causes an internal compiler
error when building with MSVC2015 with the default built
configuration. This is caused by MSVC2015's partial support for
C++14 which is required by dependencies of TF Lite. To workaround
this issue, limit Eigen to C++11 by defining EIGEN_MAX_CPP_VER=11
when building TF Lite.

Unique TensorFlower","email":"746aced590a184ef4169166e753f7c211e32e5fc@tensorflow.org"},"message":"Workaround MSVC2015 function template expansion in elementwise.

Given a function...
template<int T>
int Foo(int b)

And...
typedef int(*Bar)(int);

MSVC2015 will not see Foo<10> as the same type as Bar.

This works around the issue by instantiating wrapper methods around
elementwise::GenericPrepare() rather than using a templated
elementwise::GenericPrepare method.

Change-Id: I5378de791111b5c75592eacd0b832589252350cf","distinct":true,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Manas1820/tensorflow/commits/e83a3dbda8286609ffb8ce793fcc65dbc35c3387"},{"sha":"839928c4fcaca95eb540101f5f93a060e0995996","author":{"name":"Scott Zhu","email":"65d81eb4203ec9a5a8b298abc5184127125bc9fe@google.com"},"message":"Update keras metrics to use memory efficient alternative when collect values for evenly distributed thresholds.

This implementation is based on the example in tf.slim. It exhibits a run time and space complexity of O(T + N), where T is the number of thresholds and N is the size of predictions. Metrics that rely on standard implementation instead exhibit a complexity of O(T * N). It could save a lot of memory when N is large.

Added a unit test to verify the memory consumption. Under eager context, the ratio of memory between old and new approach is between 80 and 500. Set the limit to 50 to avoid the flakiness.

Eigen/src/Core/ArithmeticSequence.h causes an internal compiler
error when building with MSVC2015 with the default built
configuration. This is caused by MSVC2015's partial support for
C++14 which is required by dependencies of TF Lite. To workaround
this issue, limit Eigen to C++11 by defining EIGEN_MAX_CPP_VER=11
when building TF Lite.

Unique TensorFlower","email":"746aced590a184ef4169166e753f7c211e32e5fc@tensorflow.org"},"message":"Workaround MSVC2015 function template expansion in elementwise.

Given a function...
template<int T>
int Foo(int b)

And...
typedef int(*Bar)(int);

MSVC2015 will not see Foo<10> as the same type as Bar.

This works around the issue by instantiating wrapper methods around
elementwise::GenericPrepare() rather than using a templated
elementwise::GenericPrepare method.

This implementation is based on the example in tf.slim. It exhibits a run time and space complexity of O(T + N), where T is the number of thresholds and N is the size of predictions. Metrics that rely on standard implementation instead exhibit a complexity of O(T * N). It could save a lot of memory when N is large.

Added a unit test to verify the memory consumption. Under eager context, the ratio of memory between old and new approach is between 80 and 500. Set the limit to 50 to avoid the flakiness.

Unique TensorFlower","email":"746aced590a184ef4169166e753f7c211e32e5fc@tensorflow.org"},"message":"Workaround MSVC2015 function template expansion in elementwise.

Given a function...
template<int T>

elementwise::GenericPrepare() rather than using a templated
elementwise::GenericPrepare method.

This implementation is based on the example in tf.slim. It exhibits a run time and space complexity of O(T + N), where T is the number of thresholds and N is the size of predictions. Eigen/src/Core/ArithmeticSequence.h causes an internal compiler
error when building with MSVC2015 with the default built
configuration. This is caused by MSVC2015's partial support for
C++14 which is required by dependencies of TF Lite. To workaround
this issue, limit Eigen to C++11 by defining EIGEN_MAX_CPP_VER=11
when building TF Lite.

Unique TensorFlower","email":"746aced590a184ef4169166e753f7c211e32e5fc@tensorflow.org"},"message":"Workaround MSVC2015 function template expansion in elementwise.

Given a function...
template<int T>
int Foo(int b)

And...
typedef int(*Bar)(int);

MSVC2015 will not see Foo<10> as the same type as Bar.

This works around the issue by instantiating wrapper methods around
elementwise::GenericPrepare() rather than using a templated
elementwise::GenericPrepare method.

Change-Id: I5378de791111b5c75592eacd0b832589252350cf","distinct":true,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Geolem/tensorflow/commits/e83a3dbda8286609ffb8ce793fcc65dbc35c3387"},{"sha":"839928c4fcaca95eb540101f5f93a060e0995996","author":{"name":"Scott Zhu","email":"65d81eb4203ec9a5a8b298abc5184127125bc9fe@google.com"},"message":"Update keras metrics to use memory efficient alternative when collect values for evenly distributed thresholds.

This implementation is based on the example in tf.slim. It exhibits a run time and space complexity of O(T + N), where T is the number of thresholds and N is the size of predictions. Metrics that rely on standard implementation instead exhibit a complexity of O(T * N). It could save a lot of memory when N is large.

Added a unit test to verify the memory consumption. Under eager context, the ratio of memory between old and new approach is between 80 and 500. Set the limit to 50 to avoid the flakiness.

This implementation is based on the example in tf.slim. It exhibits a run time and space complexity of O(T + N), where T is the number of thresholds and N is the size of predictions. Metrics that rely on standard implementation instead exhibit a complexity of O(T * N). It could save a lot of memory when N is large.

Added a unit test to verify the memory consumption. Under eager context, the ratio of memory between old and new approach is between 80 and 500. Set the limit to 50 to avoid the flakiness.

Unique TensorFlower","email":"746aced590a184ef4169166e753f7c211e32e5fc@tensorflow.org"},"message":"Workaround MSVC2015 internal compiler errors when building Eigen.

Eigen/src/Core/ArithmeticSequence.h causes an internal compiler
error when building with MSVC2015 with the default built
configuration. This is caused by MSVC2015's partial support for
C++14 which is required by dependencies of TF Lite. To workaround
this issue, limit Eigen to C++11 by defining EIGEN_MAX_CPP_VER=11
when building TF Lite.

Unique TensorFlower","email":"746aced590a184ef4169166e753f7c211e32e5fc@tensorflow.org"},"message":"Workaround MSVC2015 function template expansion in elementwise.

Given a function...
template<int T>
int Foo(int b)

And...
typedef int(*Bar)(int);

MSVC2015 will not see Foo<10> as the same type as Bar.

This works around the issue by instantiating wrapper methods around
elementwise::GenericPrepare() rather than using a templated
elementwise::GenericPrepare method.

Change-Id: I5378de791111b5c75592eacd0b832589252350cf","distinct":true,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/smalltalkman/tensorflow/commits/e83a3dbda8286609ffb8ce793fcc65dbc35c3387"},{"sha":"839928c4fcaca95eb540101f5f93a060e0995996","author":{"name":"Scott Zhu","email":"65d81eb4203ec9a5a8b298abc5184127125bc9fe@google.com"},"message":"Update keras metrics to use memory efficient alternative when collect values for evenly distributed thresholds.

This implementation is based on the example in tf.slim. It exhibits a run time and space complexity of O(T + N), where T is the number of thresholds and N is the size of predictions. Metrics that rely on standard implementation instead exhibit a complexity of O(T * N). It could save a lot of memory when N is large.

Added a unit test to verify the memory consumption. Under eager context, the ratio of memory between old and new approach is between 80 and 500. Set the limit to 50 to avoid the flakiness.

runs, leading to nested linalg op weirdness.

This implementation is based on the example in tf.slim. It exhibits a run time and space complexity of O(T + N), where T is the number of thresholds and N is the size of predictions. Metrics that rely on standard implementation instead exhibit a complexity of O(T * N). It could save a lot of memory when N is large.

Added a unit test to verify the memory consumption. Under eager context, the ratio of memory between old and new approach is between 80 and 500. Set the limit to 50 to avoid the flakiness.

PiperOrigin-RevId: 373884147
Change-Id: I5378de791111b5c75592eacd0b832589252350cf","distinct":true,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/greedforgood/tensorflow/commits/e83a3dbda8286609ffb8ce793fcc65dbc35c3387"},{"sha":"839928c4fcaca95eb540101f5f93a060e0995996","author":{"name":"Scott Zhu","email":"65d81eb4203ec9a5a8b298abc5184127125bc9fe@google.com"},"message":"Update keras metrics to use memory efficient alternative when collect values for evenly distributed thresholds.

This implementation is based on the example in tf.slim. It exhibits a run time and space complexity of O(T + N), where T is the number of thresholds and N is the size of predictions. Metrics that rely on standard implementation instead exhibit a complexity of O(T * N). It could save a lot of memory when N is large.

Added a unit test to verify the memory consumption. Under eager context, the ratio of memory between old and new approach is between 80 and 500. Set the limit to 50 to avoid the flakiness.

Unique TensorFlower","email":"746aced590a184ef4169166e753f7c211e32e5fc@tensorflow.org"},"message":"Workaround MSVC2015 internal compiler errors when building Eigen.

Eigen/src/Core/ArithmeticSequence.h causes an internal compiler
error when building with MSVC2015 with the default built
configuration. This is caused by MSVC2015's partial support for
C++14 which is required by dependencies of TF Lite. To workaround
this issue, limit Eigen to C++11 by defining EIGEN_MAX_CPP_VER=11
when building TF Lite.

Unique TensorFlower","email":"746aced590a184ef4169166e753f7c211e32e5fc@tensorflow.org"},"message":"Workaround MSVC2015 function template expansion in elementwise.

Given a function...
template<int T>
int Foo(int b)

And...
typedef int(*Bar)(int);

MSVC2015 will not see Foo<10> as the same type as Bar.

This works around the issue by instantiating wrapper methods around
elementwise::GenericPrepare() rather than using a templated
elementwise::GenericPrepare method.

Change-Id: I5378de791111b5c75592eacd0b832589252350cf","distinct":true,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/MikeOwino/tensorflow/commits/e83a3dbda8286609ffb8ce793fcc65dbc35c3387"},{"sha":"839928c4fcaca95eb540101f5f93a060e0995996","author":{"name":"Scott Zhu","email":"65d81eb4203ec9a5a8b298abc5184127125bc9fe@google.com"},"message":"Update keras metrics to use memory efficient alternative when collect values for evenly distributed thresholds.

This implementation is based on the example in tf.slim. It exhibits a run time and space complexity of O(T + N), where T is the number of thresholds and N is the size of predictions. Metrics that rely on standard implementation instead exhibit a complexity of O(T * N). It could save a lot of memory when N is large.

Added a unit test to verify the memory consumption. Under eager context, the ratio of memory between old and new approach is between 80 and 500. Set the limit to 50 to avoid the flakiness.

Unique TensorFlower","email":"746aced590a184ef4169166e753f7c211e32e5fc@tensorflow.org"},"message":"Workaround MSVC2015 internal compiler errors when building Eigen.

Eigen/src/Core/ArithmeticSequence.h causes an internal compiler
error when building with MSVC2015 with the default built
configuration. This is caused by MSVC2015's partial support for
C++14 which is required by dependencies of TF Lite. To workaround
this issue, limit Eigen to C++11 by defining EIGEN_MAX_CPP_VER=11
when building TF Lite.

Unique TensorFlower","email":"746aced590a184ef4169166e753f7c211e32e5fc@tensorflow.org"},"message":"Workaround MSVC2015 function template expansion in elementwise.

Given a function...
template<int T>
int Foo(int b)

And...
typedef int(*Bar)(int);

MSVC2015 will not see Foo<10> as the same type as Bar.

This works around the issue by instantiating wrapper methods around
elementwise::GenericPrepare() rather than using a templated
elementwise::GenericPrepare method.

This implementation is based on the example in tf.slim. It exhibits a run time and space complexity of O(T + N), where T is the number of thresholds and N is the size of predictions. Metrics that rely on standard implementation instead exhibit a complexity of O(T * N). It could save a lot of memory when N is large.

Added a unit test to verify the memory consumption. Under eager context, the ratio of memory between old and new approach is between 80 and 500. Set the limit to 50 to avoid the flakiness.

Eigen/src/Core/ArithmeticSequence.h causes an internal compiler
error when building with MSVC2015 with the default built
configuration. This is caused by MSVC2015's partial support for
C++14 which is required by dependencies of TF Lite. To workaround
this issue, limit Eigen to C++11 by defining EIGEN_MAX_CPP_VER=11
when building TF Lite.

Unique TensorFlower","email":"746aced590a184ef4169166e753f7c211e32e5fc@tensorflow.org"},"message":"Workaround MSVC2015 function template expansion in elementwise.

Given a function...
template<int T>
int Foo(int b)

And...
typedef int(*Bar)(int);

MSVC2015 will not see Foo<10> as the same type as Bar.

This works around the issue by instantiating wrapper methods around
elementwise::GenericPrepare() rather than using a templated
elementwise::GenericPrepare method.

This implementation is based on the example in tf.slim. It exhibits a run time and space complexity of O(T + N), where T is the number of thresholds and N is the size of predictions. Metrics that rely on standard implementation instead exhibit a complexity of O(T * N). It could save a lot of memory when N is large.

Added a unit test to verify the memory consumption. Under eager context, the ratio of memory between old and new approach is between 80 and 500. Set the limit to 50 to avoid the flakiness.

Unique TensorFlower","email":"746aced590a184ef4169166e753f7c211e32e5fc@tensorflow.org"},"message":"Workaround MSVC2015 internal compiler errors when building Eigen.

Eigen/src/Core/ArithmeticSequence.h causes an internal compiler
error when building with MSVC2015 with the default built
configuration. This is caused by MSVC2015's partial support for
C++14 which is required by dependencies of TF Lite. To workaround
this issue, limit Eigen to C++11 by defining EIGEN_MAX_CPP_VER=11
when building TF Lite.

Unique TensorFlower","email":"746aced590a184ef4169166e753f7c211e32e5fc@tensorflow.org"},"message":"Workaround MSVC2015 function template expansion in elementwise.

Given a function...
template<int T>
int Foo(int b)

And...
typedef int(*Bar)(int);

MSVC2015 will not see Foo<10> as the same type as Bar.

This works around the issue by instantiating wrapper methods around
elementwise::GenericPrepare() rather than using a templated
elementwise::GenericPrepare method.

Change-Id: I5378de791111b5c75592eacd0b832589252350cf","distinct":true,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/greedisgoood/tensorflow/commits/e83a3dbda8286609ffb8ce793fcc65dbc35c3387"},{"sha":"839928c4fcaca95eb540101f5f93a060e0995996","author":{"name":"Scott Zhu","email":"65d81eb4203ec9a5a8b298abc5184127125bc9fe@google.com"},"message":"Update keras metrics to use memory efficient alternative when collect values for evenly distributed thresholds.

This implementation is based on the example in tf.slim. It exhibits a run time and space complexity of O(T + N), where T is the number of thresholds and N is the size of predictions. Metrics that rely on standard implementation instead exhibit a complexity of O(T * N). It could save a lot of memory when N is large.

Added a unit test to verify the memory consumption. Under eager context, the ratio of memory between old and new approach is between 80 and 500. Set the limit to 50 to avoid the flakiness.

Change-Id: I5378de791111b5c75592eacd0b832589252350cf","distinct":true,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/waterdrops/tensorflow/commits/e83a3dbda8286609ffb8ce793fcc65dbc35c3387"},{"sha":"839928c4fcaca95eb540101f5f93a060e0995996","author":{"name":"Scott Zhu","email":"65d81eb4203ec9a5a8b298abc5184127125bc9fe@google.com"},"message":"Update keras metrics to use memory efficient alternative when collect values for evenly distributed thresholds.

This implementation is based on the example in tf.slim. It exhibits a run time and space complexity of O(T + N), where T is the number of thresholds and N is the size of predictions. Metrics that rely on standard implementation instead exhibit a complexity of O(T * N). It could save a lot of memory when N is large.

Added a unit test to verify the memory consumption. Under eager context, the ratio of memory between old and new approach is between 80 and 500. Set the limit to 50 to avoid the flakiness.

[{"sha":"9e9a4538ddab07fbcc60882e3b4817f51e981ba3","author":{"name":"gaohuatao","email":"86377a537d75dedc160b96661fa0389dcc261c89@huawei.com"},"message":"Expand the scope of transaction in the process of deleting device

When "docker load $image" and "docker rmi $image" commands are
repeatedly executed in the background, the dockerd daemon process is
killed. As a result, the DM device where the image resides may be
unavailable. The image can be queried, but the container fails to be
run. After function “devices.issueDiscard(info)” is executed and before
function "devices.deleteTransaction(info, syncDelete)" is executed, at
this point, dockerd daemon's withdrawal would result in dm device
discarded. Howerver, the dm device is not deleted at the same time.

Ref:https://github.com/containers/storage/pull/894

Signed-off-by: gaohuatao <gaohuatao@huawei.com>","distinct":true,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gaohuatao-1/moby/commits/9e9a4538ddab07fbcc60882e3b4817f51e981ba3"}]

Eigen/src/Core/ArithmeticSequence.h causes an internal compiler
error when building with MSVC2015 with the default built
configuration. This is caused by MSVC2015's partial support for
C++14 which is required by dependencies of TF Lite. To workaround
this issue, limit Eigen to C++11 by defining EIGEN_MAX_CPP_VER=11
when building TF Lite.

Unique TensorFlower","email":"746aced590a184ef4169166e753f7c211e32e5fc@tensorflow.org"},"message":"Workaround MSVC2015 function template expansion in elementwise.

Given a function...
template<int T>

And...

elementwise::GenericPrepare() rather than using a templated
elementwise::GenericPrepare method.

Unique TensorFlower","email":"746aced590a184ef4169166e753f7c211e32e5fc@tensorflow.org"},"message":"Workaround MSVC2015 internal compiler errors when building Eigen.

Eigen/src/Core/ArithmeticSequence.h causes an internal compiler
error when building with MSVC2015 with the default built
configuration. This is caused by MSVC2015's partial support for
C++14 which is required by dependencies of TF Lite. To workaround
this issue, limit Eigen to C++11 by defining EIGEN_MAX_CPP_VER=11
when building TF Lite.

Unique TensorFlower","email":"746aced590a184ef4169166e753f7c211e32e5fc@tensorflow.org"},"message":"Workaround MSVC2015 function template expansion in elementwise.

Given a function...
template<int T>
int Foo(int b)

And...
typedef int(*Bar)(int);

MSVC2015 will not see Foo<10> as the same type as Bar.

This works around the issue by instantiating wrapper methods around
elementwise::GenericPrepare() rather than using a templated
elementwise::GenericPrepare method.

Change-Id: I5378de791111b5c75592eacd0b832589252350cf","distinct":true,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/osmaelo/tensorflow/commits/e83a3dbda8286609ffb8ce793fcc65dbc35c3387"},{"sha":"839928c4fcaca95eb540101f5f93a060e0995996","author":{"name":"Scott Zhu","email":"65d81eb4203ec9a5a8b298abc5184127125bc9fe@google.com"},"message":"Update keras metrics to use memory efficient alternative when collect values for evenly distributed thresholds.

This implementation is based on the example in tf.slim. It exhibits a run time and space complexity of O(T + N), where T is the number of thresholds and N is the size of predictions. Metrics that rely on standard implementation instead exhibit a complexity of O(T * N). It could save a lot of memory when N is large.

Added a unit test to verify the memory consumption. Under eager context, the ratio of memory between old and new approach is between 80 and 500. Set the limit to 50 to avoid the flakiness.

[{"sha":"6394d3c186602777f7a1ee942316afa2918a3362","author":{"name":"A. Unique TensorFlower","email":"746aced590a184ef4169166e753f7c211e32e5fc@tensorflow.org"},"message":"Workaround MSVC2015 internal compiler errors when building Eigen.

Eigen/src/Core/ArithmeticSequence.h causes an internal compiler
error when building with MSVC2015 with the default built
configuration. This is caused by MSVC2015's partial support for
C++14 which is required by dependencies of TF Lite. To workaround
this issue, limit Eigen to C++11 by defining EIGEN_MAX_CPP_VER=11
when building TF Lite.

Unique TensorFlower","email":"746aced590a184ef4169166e753f7c211e32e5fc@tensorflow.org"},"message":"Workaround MSVC2015 function template expansion in elementwise.

Given a function...
template<int T>
int Foo(int b)

And...
typedef int(*Bar)(int);

MSVC2015 will not see Foo<10> as the same type as Bar.

This works around the issue by instantiating wrapper methods around
elementwise::GenericPrepare() rather than using a templated
elementwise::GenericPrepare method.

This implementation is based on the example in tf.slim. It exhibits a run time and space complexity of O(T + N), where T is the number of thresholds and N is the size of predictions. Metrics that rely on standard implementation instead exhibit a complexity of O(T * N). It could save a lot of memory when N is large.

Added a unit test to verify the memory consumption. Under eager context, the ratio of memory between old and new approach is between 80 and 500. Set the limit to 50 to avoid the flakiness.

[{"sha":"6394d3c186602777f7a1ee942316afa2918a3362","author":{"name":"A. Unique TensorFlower","email":"746aced590a184ef4169166e753f7c211e32e5fc@tensorflow.org"},"message":"Workaround MSVC2015 internal compiler errors when building Eigen.

Eigen/src/Core/ArithmeticSequence.h causes an internal compiler
error when building with MSVC2015 with the default built
configuration. This is caused by MSVC2015's partial support for
C++14 which is required by dependencies of TF Lite. To workaround
this issue, limit Eigen to C++11 by defining EIGEN_MAX_CPP_VER=11
when building TF Lite.

Unique TensorFlower","email":"746aced590a184ef4169166e753f7c211e32e5fc@tensorflow.org"},"message":"Workaround MSVC2015 function template expansion in elementwise.

Given a function...
template<int T>
int Foo(int b)

And...
typedef int(*Bar)(int);

MSVC2015 will not see Foo<10> as the same type as Bar.

This works around the issue by instantiating wrapper methods around
elementwise::GenericPrepare() rather than using a templated
elementwise::GenericPrepare method.

This implementation is based on the example in tf.slim. It exhibits a run time and space complexity of O(T + N), where T is the number of thresholds and N is the size of predictions. Metrics that rely on standard implementation instead exhibit a complexity of O(T * N). It could save a lot of memory when N is large.

Added a unit test to verify the memory consumption. Under eager context, the ratio of memory between old and new approach is between 80 and 500. Set the limit to 50 to avoid the flakiness.

Unique TensorFlower","email":"746aced590a184ef4169166e753f7c211e32e5fc@tensorflow.org"},"message":"Workaround MSVC2015 internal compiler errors when building Eigen.

Eigen/src/Core/ArithmeticSequence.h causes an internal compiler
error when building with MSVC2015 with the default built
configuration. This is caused by MSVC2015's partial support for
C++14 which is required by dependencies of TF Lite. To workaround
this issue, limit Eigen to C++11 by defining EIGEN_MAX_CPP_VER=11
when building TF Lite.

Unique TensorFlower","email":"746aced590a184ef4169166e753f7c211e32e5fc@tensorflow.org"},"message":"Workaround MSVC2015 function template expansion in elementwise.

Given a function...
template<int T>
int Foo(int b)

And...
typedef int(*Bar)(int);

MSVC2015 will not see Foo<10> as the same type as Bar.

This works around the issue by instantiating wrapper methods around
elementwise::GenericPrepare() rather than using a templated
elementwise::GenericPrepare method.

Change-Id: I5378de791111b5c75592eacd0b832589252350cf","distinct":true,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/joshrose/tensorflow/commits/e83a3dbda8286609ffb8ce793fcc65dbc35c3387"},{"sha":"839928c4fcaca95eb540101f5f93a060e0995996","author":{"name":"Scott Zhu","email":"65d81eb4203ec9a5a8b298abc5184127125bc9fe@google.com"},"message":"Update keras metrics to use memory efficient alternative when collect values for evenly distributed thresholds.

This implementation is based on the example in tf.slim. It exhibits a run time and space complexity of O(T + N), where T is the number of thresholds and N is the size of predictions. Metrics that rely on standard implementation instead exhibit a complexity of O(T * N). It could save a lot of memory when N is large.

Added a unit test to verify the memory consumption. Under eager context, the ratio of memory between old and new approach is between 80 and 500. Set the limit to 50 to avoid the flakiness.

[{"sha":"6394d3c186602777f7a1ee942316afa2918a3362","author":{"name":"A. Unique TensorFlower","email":"746aced590a184ef4169166e753f7c211e32e5fc@tensorflow.org"},"message":"Workaround MSVC2015 internal compiler errors when building Eigen.

Eigen/src/Core/ArithmeticSequence.h causes an internal compiler
error when building with MSVC2015 with the default built
configuration. This is caused by MSVC2015's partial support for
C++14 which is required by dependencies of TF Lite. To workaround
this issue, limit Eigen to C++11 by defining EIGEN_MAX_CPP_VER=11
when building TF Lite.

Unique TensorFlower","email":"746aced590a184ef4169166e753f7c211e32e5fc@tensorflow.org"},"message":"Workaround MSVC2015 function template expansion in elementwise.

Given a function...
template<int T>
int Foo(int b)

And...
typedef int(*Bar)(int);

MSVC2015 will not see Foo<10> as the same type as Bar.

This works around the issue by instantiating wrapper methods around
elementwise::GenericPrepare() rather than using a templated
elementwise::GenericPrepare method.

Change-Id: I5378de791111b5c75592eacd0b832589252350cf","distinct":true,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/NeatNerdPrime/tensorflow/commits/e83a3dbda8286609ffb8ce793fcc65dbc35c3387"},{"sha":"839928c4fcaca95eb540101f5f93a060e0995996","author":{"name":"Scott Zhu","email":"65d81eb4203ec9a5a8b298abc5184127125bc9fe@google.com"},"message":"Update keras metrics to use memory efficient alternative when collect values for evenly distributed thresholds.

This implementation is based on the example in tf.slim. It exhibits a run time and space complexity of O(T + N), where T is the number of thresholds and N is the size of predictions. Metrics that rely on standard implementation instead exhibit a complexity of O(T * N). It could save a lot of memory when N is large.

Added a unit test to verify the memory consumption. Under eager context, the ratio of memory between old and new approach is between 80 and 500. Set the limit to 50 to avoid the flakiness.

Unique TensorFlower","email":"746aced590a184ef4169166e753f7c211e32e5fc@tensorflow.org"},"message":"Workaround MSVC2015 internal compiler errors when building Eigen.

Eigen/src/Core/ArithmeticSequence.h causes an internal compiler
error when building with MSVC2015 with the default built
configuration. This is caused by MSVC2015's partial support for
C++14 which is required by dependencies of TF Lite. To workaround
this issue, limit Eigen to C++11 by defining EIGEN_MAX_CPP_VER=11
when building TF Lite.

Unique TensorFlower","email":"746aced590a184ef4169166e753f7c211e32e5fc@tensorflow.org"},"message":"Workaround MSVC2015 function template expansion in elementwise.

Given a function...
template<int T>
int Foo(int b)

And...
typedef int(*Bar)(int);

MSVC2015 will not see Foo<10> as the same type as Bar.

This works around the issue by instantiating wrapper methods around
elementwise::GenericPrepare() rather than using a templated

Change-Id: I5378de791111b5c75592eacd0b832589252350cf","distinct":true,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/clayne/tensorflow/commits/e83a3dbda8286609ffb8ce793fcc65dbc35c3387"},{"sha":"839928c4fcaca95eb540101f5f93a060e0995996","author":{"name":"Scott Zhu","email":"65d81eb4203ec9a5a8b298abc5184127125bc9fe@google.com"},"message":"Update keras metrics to use memory efficient alternative when collect values for evenly distributed thresholds.

This implementation is based on the example in tf.slim. It exhibits a run time and space complexity of O(T + N), where T is the number of thresholds and N is the size of predictions. Metrics that rely on standard implementation instead exhibit a complexity of O(T * N). It could save a lot of memory when N is large.

Added a unit test to verify the memory consumption. Under eager context, the ratio of memory between old and new approach is between 80 and 500. Set the limit to 50 to avoid the flakiness.
